# Edge case: a reversible rule with ONE direction at rate=0
# Tests:  the unbinding direction is parameter-bound to 0.  RM's
#         priority-queue (Fenwick tree, FENWICK_THRESHOLD path) must
#         skip zero-propensity rules cleanly without flagging them as
#         "live" candidates for sampling.  A bug in the rule-picker
#         could either (a) divide-by-zero when normalising, (b) hang
#         on an empty event queue when only zero-rate rules remain,
#         or (c) sample the zero-rate rule and produce a wasted null
#         event that doesn't fire.  None of these have explicit
#         coverage today.
# Edge:   forward rate is high so the system rapidly shifts to the
#         bound state; with kr=0 it stays there permanently.  The
#         observable A_bound should monotonically rise to its limit
#         (min(A_tot,B_tot)).  Any reverse-direction firing — or
#         worse, a hang — is an obvious bug.
# Tier:   base
# invariant: conserved A_total = 30
# invariant: conserved B_total = 30

begin model
begin parameters
    A_tot   30
    B_tot   30
    kf      0.20
    kr      0.0      # zero-rate reverse direction
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A(s)
    B(s)
end molecule types

begin seed species
    A(s)  A_tot
    B(s)  B_tot
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_total   A()
    Molecules  B_total   B()
    Molecules  A_bound   A(s!+)
    Molecules  AB        A(s!1).B(s!1)
end observables

begin reaction rules
    A(s) + B(s) <-> A(s!1).B(s!1)  kf, kr
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>40,n_steps=>80})
end actions
